=========================================
Installing ONIE on NXP LS1088ARDB
=========================================

Cross-Compiling ONIE
====================

Change directories to ``build-config`` to compile ONIE.

To compile ONIE first change directories to ``build-config`` and then
type ``"make MACHINEROOT=../machine/nxp MACHINE=nxp_ls1088ardb all"``.  For example::

  $ cd build-config
  $ make -j4 MACHINEROOT=../machine/nxp MACHINE=nxp_ls1088ardb all

When complete, the ONIE binaries are located in
``build/images``::

Installing the ONIE binaries
============================
Step 1: Install firmwares on QSPI flash

	1> get firmware_ls1088ardb_uboot_qspiboot.img and put it in your TFTP
	wget http://www.nxp.com/lgfiles/sdk/lsdk1712/firmware_ls1088ardb_uboot_qspiboot.img

	2> Intstall the img on QSPI flash
	=> tftp a0000000 <path>/firmware_ls1088ardb_uboot_qspiboot.img
	=> sf probe 0:0
	=> sf erase 0 +$filesize && sf write 0xa0000000 0 $filesize

note: Must do step 1 before step 2 and 3

---------------------------------------------
Step 2: Install uboot (onie-nxp_ls1088ardb-r0.bin.uboot+env)

	=> tftp a0000000 <path>/onie-nxp_ls1088ardb-r0.bin.uboot+env
	=> sf probe 0:0
	=> sf erase 0x100000 +$filesize && sf write 0xa0000000 0x100000 $filesize

----------------------------------
Step 3: Install kernel (nxp_ls1088ardb-r0.itb)

	 => tftp a0000000 <path>/nxp_ls1088ardb-r0.itb
	 => sf probe 0:0
	 => sf erase 0x1000000 +$filesize && sf write 0xa0000000 0x1000000 $filesize

----------------------------------
Step 4 -- Configure Serial Console

	ONIE defaults the serial console baud rate to 115200.  You may need to
	adjust your terminal settings.

----------------------------
Step 5 -- Restart The System

	You can interrupt the boot process by pressing any key during the
	count down::

	=> reset
